# SECRET_SCAN_ALLOWLIST
# Paths excluded from the CHECK 9 secret scan in validate.sh.
# One path prefix per line. Lines starting with # are comments.
#
# Rules:
# - Use the narrowest possible prefix (specific file, not a directory)
# - Do NOT add entire directories like docs/ or *.md — that defeats the check
# - New fixtures/examples containing flagged patterns (ghp_, JWT-like strings, etc.)
#   should be added here with a comment explaining why they are safe
# - Allowlist changes must be reviewed in PR like any other code
#
# Example (uncomment to use):
# docs/examples/auth-tokens.md   # contains example ghp_ token in curl snippet

scripts/validate.sh
scripts/SECRET_SCAN_ALLOWLIST
